A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Public Utilities – Energy Generation
3 FOR the purpose of stating the authority to construct, permit, and operate in the State an
4 energy generating system that produces energy from natural gas; stating the
5 General Assembly’s support for the development of additional nuclear energy in the
6 State; stating that the General Assembly encourages PJM Interconnection, LLC to
7 provide an expedited interconnection process for new thermal generation resources
8 in the State; and generally relating to energy generation in the State.
9 BY adding to
10 Article – Public Utilities
11 Section 7–218
12 Annotated Code of Maryland
13 (2020 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
14 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
15 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
16 Article – Public Utilities
17 7–218.
18 (A) NOTWITHSTANDING ANY OTHER PROVISION OF LAW, AND SUBJECT TO
19 SUBSECTION (B) OF THIS SECTION, ENERGY GENERATING SYSTEMS THAT PRODUCE
20 ENERGY FROM NATURAL GAS MAY BE CONSTRUCTED, PERMITTED, AND OPERATED
21 IN THE STATE.
22 (B) A PERSON CONSTRUCTING AN ENERGY GENERATING SYSTEM UNDER
23 THIS SECTION SHALL COMPLY WITH THE PROVISIONS OF THIS SUBTITLE RELATING
24 TO REQUIREMENTS TO OBTAIN:
