2 SENATE BILL 643
1 (1) A CERTIFICATE OF PUBLIC CONVENIENCE AND NECESSITY; OR
2 (2) COMMISSION APPROVAL FOR THE CONSTRUCTION OF THE
3 GENERATING SYSTEM.
4 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That:
5 (1) the General Assembly supports the development of additional nuclear
6 energy in the State, including small modular reactors and the combination of nuclear
7 energy and energy produced from natural gas, for reliable clean energy in the State; and
8 (2) the General Assembly encourages PJM Interconnection, LLC to provide
9 an expedited interconnection process for new thermal generation resources in the State.
10 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
11 October 1, 2025.

